0.1 mL Co2+-CDs solution (15 mg/mL) and 0.1 mL R-CDs solution (5 mg/mL) was mixed thoroughly with 9.7 mL buffer solution (pH = 3–7) and 0.1 mL NO2
                        − standard solution (10 mM) (Fig. 1
                        ). The various pH solutions were prepared by acetic acid and sodium acetate solutions. The fluorescence ratio F436/F671 were measured in different pH at room temperature, which F436 and F671 denoted the fluorescent intensity of Co2+-CDs@R-CDs in 436 nm and 671 nm respectively. All fluorescence spectra were recorded in a range from 395 nm to 700 nm with excitation at 380 nm with the excitation and emission bandwidths of 5.0 nm and 5.0 nm separately.
